ItemDef.def:Label: Study Identifier

ItemDef.Comment: Subject identification unique across all trials
ItemDef.def:Label: Unique Subject Identifier

ItemDef.Name: VISIT
ItemDef.Comment: See Note 1
ItemDef.def:Label: Visit Name

ItemDef.Name: VISITNUM
ItemDef.Comment: See Note 1
ItemDef.def:Label: Visit Number

ItemDef.Name: VSBLFL
ItemDef.Comment: Set equal to "Y" I if the test assessment is the last non-missing before first dose. Missing otherwise.
ItemDef.def:Label: Baseline Flag

ItemDef.Name: VSDRVFL
ItemDef.Comment: Set equal to 'Y' when VSTESTCD='BSA' or 'BMI'.
ItemDef.def:Label: Derived Flag

ItemDef.Name: VSDTC
ItemDef.Comment: Vital signs measurement date (ISO 8601 format).
ItemDef.def:Label: Date/Time of Measurements

ItemDef.Name: VSDY
ItemDef.Comment: Derived from the vital signs test date and reference start date. Calculated as (date part of VSDTC - DM.RFSTDT) + 1, if the vital signs test date is on or after the reference start date. Otherwise, if the vital signs test date is prior to the reference start date, then calculated as (date part of VSDTC - DM.RFSTDT). See Note 2
ItemDef.def:Label: Study day of Vital Signs

ItemDef.Name: VSMETHOD
ItemDef.Comment: See Note 5
ItemDef.def:Label: Method of Test or Examination

ItemDef.Name: VSORRES
ItemDef.Comment: CRF values for all but BSA and BMI. BMI=10000*(weight / height**2). BSA=SQRT(weight*height/3600).
ItemDef.def:Label: Result or Finding in Original Units

ItemDef.Name: VSORRESU
ItemDef.Comment: See Note 5
ItemDef.def:Label: Original Units

ItemDef.Name: VSSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Derived: a unique incremental sequence number, beginning with 1 and adding 1, for each unique occurrence of a subject, visit, vital signs test and vital signs date record.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: VSSTRESC
ItemDef.Comment: Set equal to VSORRES apart from BMI and BSA. For BMI and BSA this is the character representation of the derived numeric value VSSTRESN.
ItemDef.def:Label: Character Result/Finding in Std Format

ItemDef.Name: VSSTRESN
ItemDef.Comment: Numeric representation of VSORRES for all values apart from BSA and BMI. The values for BMI and BSA were derived as numeric.
ItemDef.def:Label: Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units

ItemDef.Name: VSSTRESU
ItemDef.Comment: Set equal to VSORRESU for all values apart from BSA and BMI. The values for BMI and BSA were derived as standard units.
ItemDef.def:Label: Standard Units

ItemDef.Name: VSTEST
ItemDef.Comment: See Note 5
ItemDef.def:Label: Vital Signs Test Name

ItemDef.Name: VSTESTCD
ItemDef.Comment: Short version of VSTEST. See Note 5
ItemDef.def:Label: Vital Signs Test Short Name

ItemDef.Name: AECOLGR
ItemDef.Comment: The CRF allows for Grades 1-4. Fatal outcome AEs with Grade 4 CRF classification were re-classified as Grade 5. This variable contains the original value prior to recoding of fatal Grade 4 AEs. There is one subject (USUBJID = '006193-158-003-002') that had a grade 5 in the raw database for a fatal AE with AETERM='DEATH-DIEASE PROGRESSION NOS'. Possible values are missing or:"GRADE 1","GRADE 2","GRADE 3","GRADE 4","GRADE 5".
ItemDef.def:Label: Standard Toxicity Grade as Collected

ItemDef.Name: AECOLGRN
ItemDef.Comment: Numeric representation of AECOLGR.
ItemDef.def:Label: Standard Toxicity Grade Numeric Code as

ItemDef.Name: AEDICTVS
ItemDef.Comment: Value is MedDRA 12.0.
ItemDef.def:Label: AE Dictionary Version

ItemDef.Name: AEDTHDTC
ItemDef.Comment: Death date in ISO 8601 format.
ItemDef.def:Label: Date/Time of Death

ItemDef.Name: AEHLGT
ItemDef.Comment: From MedDRA 12.0 dictionary.
ItemDef.def:Label: High Level Group Term

ItemDef.Name: AEHLT
ItemDef.Comment: From MedDRA 12.0 dictionary.
ItemDef.def:Label: High Level Term

ItemDef.Name: AELLT
ItemDef.Comment: From MedDRA 12.0 dictionary.
ItemDef.def:Label: Lowest Level Term

ItemDef.Name: AEOVISIT
ItemDef.Comment: This is the original visit collected. It differs from the variable VISIT for unscheduled visits where it was possible to reassign to the actual cycle for VISIT based on the visit date in the SV domain. See Note 1
ItemDef.def:Label: Original Visit Name

ItemDef.Name: AEREFER
ItemDef.Comment: AE initial ref. number.
ItemDef.def:Label: AE Reference number

ItemDef.Name: AETOXGRN
ItemDef.Comment: Numeric representation of AETOXGR.
ItemDef.def:Label: Standard Toxicity Grade Numeric Code

ItemDef.Name: AETRTEM
ItemDef.Comment: N: Pre-treatment,T: Treatment emergent,P: Post-treatment. If visit is baseline visit (Visitnum = 1), then it is "Pre-Treatment". If visit is between visit 1 and visit 80, then it is "Treatment Emergent". if the visit is after visit 80, then it "Post-Treatment."
ItemDef.def:Label: Treatment Emergent Classification

ItemDef.Name: CMATCL1
ItemDef.Comment: Dictionary-derived variable.
ItemDef.def:Label: Selected Anatomic Class

ItemDef.Name: CMATCL2
ItemDef.Comment: Dictionary-derived variable.
ItemDef.def:Label: Selected Therapeutic Class

ItemDef.Name: CMATCSEL
ItemDef.Comment: Dictionary-derived variable.
ItemDef.def:Label: Selected ATC Code

ItemDef.Name: ENDTCOL
ItemDef.Comment: This is the collected end date/time when it is less than start date/time.
ItemDef.def:Label: Collected End Date/Time of Medication

ItemDef.Name: ARM2
ItemDef.Comment: If a subject was randomized but never treated, the value of ARM is "NOT ASSIGNED" and the value of ARM2 is the original planned arm. This is to comply with SDTM IG 3.1.1. See Note 9
ItemDef.def:Label: Original Description of Planned Arm

ItemDef.Name: ARMA
ItemDef.Comment: Recieved treatment arm. Possible values are: "MITOXANTRONE/PREDNISONE", "XRP6258/PREDNISONE".
ItemDef.def:Label: Description of Actually Received Arm

ItemDef.Name: ARMCD2
ItemDef.Comment: If a subject was randomized but never treated, the value of ARMCD is "NOTASSGN" and the value of ARMCD2 is the original planned arm code. This is to comply with SDTM IG 3.1.1. See Note 9
ItemDef.def:Label: Original Planned Arm Code

ItemDef.Name: BSABL
ItemDef.Comment: Body Surface Area at baseline. It is calculated as: BSABL=sqrt(height*weight)/3600). Note, weight in the formula refers to baseline weight. However, if weight at baseline is missing, then weight at visit 1 is used instead.
ItemDef.def:Label: Baseline Body Surface Area (m2)

ItemDef.Name: ITT
ItemDef.Comment: Derived: if the subject was randomized then value is "Y". Otherwise "N".
ItemDef.def:Label: Intent-to-treat Population

ItemDef.Name: PPROT
ItemDef.Comment: Set equal to the safety population.
ItemDef.def:Label: Per Protocol Population

ItemDef.Name: SAFETY
ItemDef.Comment: Derived: if the subject received any study treatment then the value is "Y". Otherwise "N".
ItemDef.def:Label: Safety Population

ItemDef.Name: ENDTCOL
ItemDef.Comment: This is the collected end date/time when it is less than start date/time.
ItemDef.def:Label: Collected End Date/Time of Treatment

ItemDef.Name: EXCUMD
ItemDef.Comment: Derived: the cumulative dose received for each subject across all visits. EXCUMD equals the CRF total dose given variable, EXDOSE, at the subjects first treatment visit. For each subsequent treatment visit, the value of EXCUMD is incremented by the value of the CRF total dose given variable, EXDOSE. For a subjects last treatment visit record, the EXCUMD value will be equal to the total dose received for that subject during the study.
ItemDef.def:Label: Cumulative Dose

ItemDef.Name: EXCUMD2
ItemDef.Comment: Derived: the cumulative dose received for each subject across all visits. EXCUMD2 equals the calculated dose, EXDOSE2, at the subjects first treatment visit. For each subsequent treatment visit, the value of EXCUMD2 is incremented by the value of the calculated dose, EXDOSE2. For a subjects last treatment visit record, the EXCUMD2 value will be equal to the total calculated dose received for that subject during the study.
ItemDef.def:Label: Cumulative Dose in mg/m2

ItemDef.Name: EXDELAY
ItemDef.Comment: Derived as the days elasped between treatment cycles. The days elapsed is the difference between the current cycles start date and the previous cycles theoretical end date. For a subjects first treatment cycle, the treatment delay value will be set equal to zero. Calculated as (date part of EXSTDTC - previous cycles theoretical end date).
ItemDef.def:Label: Number of Days Treatment Delayed

ItemDef.Name: EXDOSE2
ItemDef.Comment: Relative dose calculated as EXDOSE/BSA. BSA is in dataset VS where VSTESTCD="BSA".
ItemDef.def:Label: Dose per Administration Per BSA

ItemDef.Name: EXPDOSE2
ItemDef.Comment: Set equal to EXDOSE2*100/25 when EXTRT is equal to 'XRP6258'; Set equal to EXDOSE2*100/12 when EXTRT is equal to 'MITOXANTRONE'.
ItemDef.def:Label: % of Dose per Administration Per BSA

ItemDef.Name: EXPDOSU
ItemDef.Comment: Set equal to 'mg/m2'.
ItemDef.def:Label: Planned Dose Units Per Administration

ItemDef.Name: EXTINT
ItemDef.Comment: Derived: cumulative total dose in mg/m2 divided by toal duration, calculated as EXCUMD2/EXTDURN.
ItemDef.def:Label: Total Dose Intensity

ItemDef.Name: EXTRINT
ItemDef.Comment: Derived: calculated as EXTINT*3*100/12 when EXTRT equals to'MITOXANTRONE'; or as EXTINT*3*100/25 when EXTRT equals to 'XRP6258'.
ItemDef.def:Label: Total Dose Rel to Plan Dose Intensity

ItemDef.Name: IETEST1
ItemDef.Comment: Continuation of IETEST.
ItemDef.def:Label: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Continued

ItemDef.Name: LBOVISIT
ItemDef.Comment: This is the original visit collected. It differs from the variable VISIT for unscheduled visits where it was possible to reassign to the actual cycle for VISIT based on the visit date in the SV domain. See Note 1
ItemDef.def:Label: Original Visit Name
